            <Paragraph>
               

                <Bold FontSize="24">Columns:</Bold>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>If-Else-End If</Bold> - If is used for conditional branching. Here are the columns:
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        1. Sequence
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Sequence is a decimal number with 4 digits after the decimal. It can be modified to allow you to insert rows anywhere in your script. Rows are executed in sequence number order.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        2. Verb
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The verb can be If, Else, or End If.  Every If must be eventually followed by an End If. If there are is an Else verb occurring before the End If, everything before the Else will be executed if the condition on the If action is true and then execution will jump to the statement after the End If.  However, if the condition is false, everything between the Else and End If will be executed before proceeding to the statement after the End If.  If there is no Else involved, the statement between the If and the End If only execute if the condition of the If statement is true.
            </Paragraph>


            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
